title: Share of economic sectors in the global gross domestic product from 2007 to 2017
summary: The given chart is of multi-line type with 3 lines namely Agriculture, Industry, and Services. The y axis represents Share of GDP and the x axis represents Year.
Overall Services is gradually increasing, Agriculture, and Industry are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The lines ordered according to average values of Share of GDP in descending order is: 1. Services, 2. Industry, and lastly, 3. Agriculture.
Overall across the Year, Services mostly maintained the highest Share of GDP when compared to others with a mean value of 63.62, and it peaked at 2016.
Followed by Industry which ranks as the second topmpost line , with an average of 26.7 Share of GDP,reaching its highest point  at 2007 with a value of 28.5.
The botommost line, Agriculture,  has a mean of 3.63, and peaked at 2007.
